quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  17,85,"And they ask thee regarding the spirit, Say thou: the spirit is by the command of my Lord, and ye have not been vouchsafed of knowledge save a little"
  17,86,"And if We listed, We could surely take away that which We have revealed unto thee: then thou wilt not find in respect thereof against us as trustee"
  17,87,Except as a mercy from thy Lord verily His grace unto thee is ever great
  17,88,"Say thou: if the mankind and the jinn leagued together that they might produce the like of this Qur'an, they could nor produce the like thereof, though one to the other were a backer"
  17,89,"And assuredly We have variously propounded for mankind in this Qur'an every kind of similitude, yet most men have refused everything except infidelity"
  17,90,"And they say: we shall by no means believe in thee until thou causest for us to gush forth from the earth a foun tain"
  17,91,"Or there be for thee a garden of date-palms and wine, and thou causest in the midst thereof rivers to gush forth"
  17,92,"Or thou causest the heaven to fall upon us, as thou assertest, in pieces, or thou bringest God and the angels face to face"
  17,93,"Or there be for thee a house of gold or thou mountest to the heaven, and we will by no means believe in thy mounting even until thou causest a book to be sent down to us, which we may read. Say thou: hallowed be my Lord! I am naught but a human being sent as an apostle"